The article is about Jill Biden, the First Lady of the United States, wishing a happy Diwali to Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and Buddhists celebrating the Festival of Lights. She mentions that the White House is hosting an official Diwali reception and highlights the diversity of the current administration, led by Vice President Kamala Harris, who is the first Black American and South Asian American to hold the position. Jill Biden expresses gratitude for the optimism, courage, and empathy shown by the South Asian community, emphasizing their contribution to the nation's progress. She acknowledges the ongoing struggle for equality in American history and emphasizes that Diwali serves as a reminder of the power to bring light to the world. The article concludes with well wishes for those celebrating Diwali to enjoy the festivities and embrace the sense of community.